               <p>WILLIAM WILSON. I am a <rs id="t18320405-254-viclabel1502" type="occupation">mariner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-254-victim2163 t18320405-254-viclabel1502"></join>. I lost the articles stated out of the cabin of my vessel, which lays in the river; the prisoner was on board - I told him I had missed them, but I have never seen them since.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-254-person2164">
                  JOHN 
                  REED
               <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2164" type="surname" value="REED"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2164" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2164" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am mate on board the ship. The prisoner was an <rs id="t18320405-254-deflabel1503" type="occupation">apprentice on board</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320405-254-defend2161 t18320405-254-deflabel1503"></join> - I know there was nothing lost out of the shop till he came on board; the prosecutor lost a pair of shoes, two shirts and a frock on the 22nd of March; I questioned the prisoner about them; he gave me no answer - I asked where he slept; he said at home; I said I would send to his father, which I did - he then absconded from the ship, and was not taken for same case; I then asked him what he had sold the shoes for, and he said half a crown.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320405-254-person2165">
                  JOHN 
                  LITTLE
               <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2165" type="surname" value="LITTLE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2165" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320405-254-person2165" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Thames Police-officer. I took the prisoner - I said he was charged with stealing Wilson's clothes; he said he had sold them to different Jews in Houndsditch - I went with him there, but he could not point them out.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. This is the first time I ever stood at a bar; I hope you will have mercy.</p>
